match.name: Desert Chaos
match.about:
Match Directors:
Scott Woodhouse - Co-MD
Tanner Balderree - Co-MD

We are proud to present the first annual Desert Chaos Match, being held in sunny southern
Utah. This match is an extremely scenic match with natural terrain, unique props, and gorgeous
landscapes of red rock cliffs to look at between stages.
Shooters will be put through a challenging and fun course of fire across 18 stages and
approximately 200 rounds (not including zero and dope checks on registration day). Zero
boards will be available during the match at multiple locations. Shooters will be stressed with
time, movement, unique positions, and targets…but not all at once. Shooters will need to be
solid on target acquisition, finding their targets across the red rock and natural landscape.
Location:
Private land located 25 minutes outside of Hurricane, UT
(A Google maps pin will be provided to those that register)
Schedule:
Friday, March 6th - Registration and Zero
12:00-5:00PM - Zero board and steel at distance will be available to shoot and reference dope.
Match books and match bags will be handed out during registration. Shooters may walk the
course of fire with the match book. Putting rifle on props or shooting off props will NOT be
permitted.
Saturday, March 7th - Day 1 (10 stages)
7:00AM - Late registration and zero board
8:00AM - Mandatory safety brief and match overview.
8:30AM - Range hot
11:30AM - Provided Lunch
Sunday, March 8th - Day 2 and Awards (8 stages)
7:30 - On stage ready to begin match
7:45AM - Range hot
Banquet and Awards to follow
Registration Details:
Match Fee - $300 (non-refundable)

Match fees are non-refundable and cannot be transferred to another match. Please coordinate
with the MD’s if you wish to sell your slot to another shooter.
Squadding:
Squadding will open in mid-Feburary and will be completed through Impact Scoring. We will
send out a reminder email leading up to this date and another email as squadding opens up.
Travel & Lodging:
Airports

St. George: St. George Regional Airport (SGU) - 30 mins to Hurricane, UT (24 miles)
Las Vegas: Harry Reid International Airport (LAS) - 2 hours to Hurricane, UT (140 miles)
Salt Lake City: Salt Lake Int. Airport (SLC) - 4 hours to Hurricane, UT (294 miles)

Hotels:
-
Due to being located close to Zions National Park, southern Utah has many options for
hotels between St. George, Washington and Hurricane. If there are any issues finding
lodging, please reach out to Tanner Balderree at the email below.
The private land we shoot on is not available to camp or park trailers on. However, there are
plenty of campgrounds and BLM land around Hurricane that shooters can utilize to camp.

Any lodging/camping questions may be addressed at t.balderree89@gmail.com
